headline: Realtor.com速 November Rental Report: Even with Rent Declines, Minimum Wage Earners Need Extended Hours to Afford Rents
summary: Rents declined in November, falling by -1.1% year over year to a median of $1,703, according to the Realtor.com速 November Rental Report released today. Despite the dip in rents, affordability remains a concern, with minimum wage earners requiring extended working hours to afford a typical rental unit in 44 of the top 50 metros in the United States.
